1 /*
2 ** ###################################################################
3 ** Compilers: Keil ARM C/C++ Compiler
4 ** Freescale C/C++ for Embedded ARM
5 ** GNU C Compiler
6 ** IAR ANSI C/C++ Compiler for ARM
7 **
8 ** Reference manual: K70P256M150SF3RM, Rev. 2, Dec 2011
9 ** Version: rev. 1.12, 2013-10-29
10 ** Build: b150309
11 **
12 ** Abstract:
13 ** This header file implements peripheral memory map for MK70F12
14 ** processor.
15 **
16 ** Copyright (c) 1997 - 2013 Freescale Semiconductor, Inc.
17 ** All Rights Reserved.
18 **
19 ** http: www.freescale.com
20 ** mail: support@freescale.com
21 **
22 ** Revisions:
23 ** - rev. 1.0 (2011-08-12)
24 ** Initial version.
25 ** - rev. 1.1 (2011-09-23)
26 ** Fixed number of slave registers of AXBS module.
27 ** - rev. 1.2 (2011-11-03)
28 ** Registers updated according to the new reference manual revision - Rev. 1, Oct 2011
29 ** Registers of the following modules have been updated - CAN, DDR, I2S, LCDC, MCG, MPU, NFC, RCM, RTC, SIM, USBHS, WDOG
30 ** - rev. 1.3 (2011-11-10)
31 ** Support of ARM Keil compiler added.
32 ** - rev. 1.4 (2011-11-18)
33 ** SDHC - bit group WRBRSTLEN from the SDHC_WML register removed.
34 ** - rev. 1.5 (2012-01-04)
35 ** Registers updated according to the new reference manual revision - Rev. 2, Dec 2011
36 ** EWM - INTEN bit in EWM_CTRL register has been added.
37 ** PDB - register PDB_PO0EN renamed to PRB_POEN.
38 ** PMC - BGEN bit in PMC_REGSC register has been removed.
39 ** SIM - several changes in SCGC registers. Bit USBHS in SOPT2 register removed.
40 ** UART - new bits RXOFE in regiter CFIFO and RXOF in register SFIFO.
41 ** DRY - bit THYD in CR register renamed to THYS. Bit group KSL in LR register removed.
42 ** LCDC - bits GWLPM in LSR register, ERR_RES_EN, GW_ERR_RES_EN in LIER and ERR_RES, GW_ERR_RES in LISR removed.
43 ** - rev. 1.6 (2012-04-13)
44 ** Added new #define symbol MCU_MEM_MAP_VERSION_MINOR.
45 ** Added new #define symbols <peripheralType>_BASE_PTRS.
46 ** - rev. 1.7 (2012-07-09)
47 ** UART1 - Fixed register definition - ISO7816 registers added.
48 ** - rev. 1.8 (2012-09-17)
49 ** DRY module removed.
50 ** - rev. 1.9 (2012-10-19)
51 ** RTC - security related registers removed.
52 ** - rev. 1.10 (2013-04-05)
53 ** Changed start of doxygen comment.
54 ** - rev. 1.11 (2013-06-24)
55 ** MPU - missing region descriptor registers added.
56 ** SCB - register CPACR added.
57 ** - rev. 1.12 (2013-10-29)
58 ** Definition of BITBAND macros updated to support peripherals with 32-bit acces disabled.
59 **
60 ** ###################################################################
61 */

734  uint32_t PACRH;
735  uint32_t PACRI;
736  uint32_t PACRJ;

738  uint32_t PACRL;
739  uint32_t PACRM;
740  uint32_t PACRN;
741  uint32_t PACRO;
742  uint32_t PACRP;

1703 typedef struct AXBS_MemMap {
1704  struct { /* offset: 0x0, array step: 0x100 */
1705  uint32_t PRS;
1706  uint8_t RESERVED_0[12];
1707  uint32_t CRS;
1708  uint8_t RESERVED_1[236];
1709  } SLAVE[8];
1710  uint32_t MGPCR0;
1711  uint8_t RESERVED_0[252];
1712  uint32_t MGPCR1;
1713  uint8_t RESERVED_1[252];
1714  uint32_t MGPCR2;
1715  uint8_t RESERVED_2[252];
1716  uint32_t MGPCR3;
1717  uint8_t RESERVED_3[252];
1718  uint32_t MGPCR4;
1719  uint8_t RESERVED_4[252];
1720  uint32_t MGPCR5;
1721  uint8_t RESERVED_5[252];
1722  uint32_t MGPCR6;
1723  uint8_t RESERVED_6[252];
1724  uint32_t MGPCR7;
1725 } volatile *AXBS_MemMapPtr;

1900 
1907 typedef struct CAN_MemMap {
1908  uint32_t MCR;
1909  uint32_t CTRL1;
1910  uint32_t TIMER;
1911  uint8_t RESERVED_0[4];
1912  uint32_t RXMGMASK;
1913  uint32_t RX14MASK;
1914  uint32_t RX15MASK;
1915  uint32_t ECR;
1916  uint32_t ESR1;
1917  uint32_t IMASK2;
1918  uint32_t IMASK1;
1919  uint32_t IFLAG2;
1920  uint32_t IFLAG1;
1921  uint32_t CTRL2;
1922  uint32_t ESR2;
1923  uint8_t RESERVED_1[8];
1924  uint32_t CRCR;
1925  uint32_t RXFGMASK;
1926  uint32_t RXFIR;
1927  uint8_t RESERVED_2[48];
1928  struct { /* offset: 0x80, array step: 0x10 */
1929  uint32_t CS;
1930  uint32_t ID;
1931  uint32_t WORD0;
1932  uint32_t WORD1;
1933  } MB[16];
1934  uint8_t RESERVED_3[1792];
1935  uint32_t RXIMR[16];
1936 } volatile *CAN_MemMapPtr;
1937

1951 #define CAN_TIMER_REG(base) ((base)->TIMER)
1952 #define CAN_RXMGMASK_REG(base) ((base)->RXMGMASK)

1954 #define CAN_RX15MASK_REG(base) ((base)->RX15MASK)
1955 #define CAN_ECR_REG(base) ((base)->ECR)
1956 #define CAN_ESR1_REG(base) ((base)->ESR1)
1957 #define CAN_IMASK2_REG(base) ((base)->IMASK2)
1958 #define CAN_IMASK1_REG(base) ((base)->IMASK1)
1959 #define CAN_IFLAG2_REG(base) ((base)->IFLAG2)
1960 #define CAN_IFLAG1_REG(base) ((base)->IFLAG1)
1961 #define CAN_CTRL2_REG(base) ((base)->CTRL2)
1962 #define CAN_ESR2_REG(base) ((base)->ESR2)
1963 #define CAN_CRCR_REG(base) ((base)->CRCR)
1964 #define CAN_RXFGMASK_REG(base) ((base)->RXFGMASK)

3458 typedef struct CRC_MemMap {
3459  union { /* offset: 0x0 */
3460  struct { /* offset: 0x0 */
3461  uint16_t CRCL;
3462  uint16_t CRCH;
3463  } ACCESS16BIT;
3464  uint32_t CRC;
3465  struct { /* offset: 0x0 */
3466  uint8_t CRCLL;
3467  uint8_t CRCLU;
3468  uint8_t CRCHL;
3469  uint8_t CRCHU;
3470  } ACCESS8BIT;
3471  };
3472  union { /* offset: 0x4 */
3473  struct { /* offset: 0x4 */
3474  uint16_t GPOLYL;
3475  uint16_t GPOLYH;
3476  } GPOLY_ACCESS16BIT;
3477  uint32_t GPOLY;
3478  struct { /* offset: 0x4 */
3479  uint8_t GPOLYLL;
3480  uint8_t GPOLYLU;
3481  uint8_t GPOLYHL;
3482  uint8_t GPOLYHU;
3483  } GPOLY_ACCESS8BIT;
3484  };
3485  union { /* offset: 0x8 */
3486  uint32_t CTRL;
3487  struct { /* offset: 0x8 */
3488  uint8_t RESERVED_0[3];
3489  uint8_t CTRLHU;
3490  } CTRL_ACCESS8BIT;
3491  };
3492 } volatile *CRC_MemMapPtr;

9250 typedef struct FTM_MemMap {
9251  uint32_t SC;
9252  uint32_t CNT;
9253  uint32_t MOD;
9254  struct { /* offset: 0xC, array step: 0x8 */
9255  uint32_t CnSC;
9256  uint32_t CnV;
9257  } CONTROLS[8];
9258  uint32_t CNTIN;
9259  uint32_t STATUS;
9260  uint32_t MODE;
9261  uint32_t SYNC;
9262  uint32_t OUTINIT;
9263  uint32_t OUTMASK;
9264  uint32_t COMBINE;
9265  uint32_t DEADTIME;
9266  uint32_t EXTTRIG;
9267  uint32_t POL;
9268  uint32_t FMS;
9269  uint32_t FILTER;
9270  uint32_t FLTCTRL;
9271  uint32_t QDCTRL;
9272  uint32_t CONF;
9273  uint32_t FLTPOL;
9274  uint32_t SYNCONF;
9275  uint32_t INVCTRL;
9276  uint32_t SWOCTRL;
9277  uint32_t PWMLOAD;
9278 } volatile *FTM_MemMapPtr;

10726 typedef struct ITM_MemMap {
10727  union { /* offset: 0x0 */
10728  uint32_t STIM_READ[32];
10729  uint32_t STIM_WRITE[32];
10730  };
10731  uint8_t RESERVED_0[3456];
10732  uint32_t TER;
10733  uint8_t RESERVED_1[60];
10734  uint32_t TPR;
10735  uint8_t RESERVED_2[60];
10736  uint32_t TCR;
10737  uint8_t RESERVED_3[300];
10738  uint32_t LAR;
10739  uint32_t LSR;
10740  uint8_t RESERVED_4[24];
10741  uint32_t PID4;
10742  uint32_t PID5;
10743  uint32_t PID6;
10744  uint32_t PID7;
10745  uint32_t PID0;
10746  uint32_t PID1;
10747  uint32_t PID2;
10748  uint32_t PID3;
10749  uint32_t CID0;
10750  uint32_t CID1;
10751  uint32_t CID2;
10752  uint32_t CID3;
10753 } volatile *ITM_MemMapPtr;

12478 
12485 typedef struct MPU_MemMap {
12486  uint32_t CESR;
12487  uint8_t RESERVED_0[12];
12488  struct { /* offset: 0x10, array step: 0x8 */
12489  uint32_t EAR;
12490  uint32_t EDR;
12491  } SP[5];
12492  uint8_t RESERVED_1[968];
12493  uint32_t WORD[16][4];
12494  uint8_t RESERVED_2[768];
12495  uint32_t RGDAAC[16];
12496 } volatile *MPU_MemMapPtr;
12497

12511 #define MPU_EDR_REG(base,index) ((base)->SP[index].EDR)
12512 #define MPU_WORD_REG(base,index,index2) ((base)->WORD[index][index2])
12513 #define MPU_RGDAAC_REG(base,index) ((base)->RGDAAC[index])

17085 typedef struct SPI_MemMap {
17086  uint32_t MCR;
17087  uint8_t RESERVED_0[4];
17088  uint32_t TCR;
17089  union { /* offset: 0xC */
17090  uint32_t CTAR[2];
17091  uint32_t CTAR_SLAVE[1];
17092  };
17093  uint8_t RESERVED_1[24];
17094  uint32_t SR;
17095  uint32_t RSER;
17096  union { /* offset: 0x34 */
17097  uint32_t PUSHR;
17098  uint32_t PUSHR_SLAVE;
17099  };
17100  uint32_t POPR;
17101  uint32_t TXFR0;
17102  uint32_t TXFR1;
17103  uint32_t TXFR2;
17104  uint32_t TXFR3;
17105  uint8_t RESERVED_2[48];
17106  uint32_t RXFR0;
17107  uint32_t RXFR1;
17108  uint32_t RXFR2;
17109  uint32_t RXFR3;
17110 } volatile *SPI_MemMapPtr;

18734 typedef struct USB_MemMap {

18745  uint8_t OTGICR;

18747  uint8_t OTGSTAT;

18749  uint8_t OTGCTL;
18750  uint8_t RESERVED_7[99];
18751  uint8_t ISTAT;
18752  uint8_t RESERVED_8[3];
18753  uint8_t INTEN;
18754  uint8_t RESERVED_9[3];
18755  uint8_t ERRSTAT;
18756  uint8_t RESERVED_10[3];
18757  uint8_t ERREN;
18758  uint8_t RESERVED_11[3];
18759  uint8_t STAT;
18760  uint8_t RESERVED_12[3];
18761  uint8_t CTL;

18764  uint8_t RESERVED_14[3];

18776  uint8_t RESERVED_20[3];
18777  uint8_t BDTPAGE3;

18779  struct { /* offset: 0xC0, array step: 0x4 */
18780  uint8_t ENDPT;
